1 The proverbs of Solomon.
A wise son makes a glad father;
but a foolish son brings grief to his mother.
  -- Proverbs 10:1 , World English Bible
%
2 Treasures of wickedness profit nothing,
but righteousness delivers from death.
  -- Proverbs 10:2 , World English Bible
%
3 Yahweh will not allow the soul of the righteous to go hungry,
but he thrusts away the desire of the wicked.
  -- Proverbs 10:3 , World English Bible
%
4 He becomes poor who works with a lazy hand,
but the hand of the diligent brings wealth.
  -- Proverbs 10:4 , World English Bible
%
5 He who gathers in summer is a wise son,
but he who sleeps during the harvest is a son who causes shame.
  -- Proverbs 10:5 , World English Bible
%
6 Blessings are on the head of the righteous,
but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
  -- Proverbs 10:6 , World English Bible
%
7 The memory of the righteous is blessed,
but the name of the wicked will rot.
  -- Proverbs 10:7 , World English Bible
%
8 The wise in heart accept commandments,
but a chattering fool will fall.
  -- Proverbs 10:8 , World English Bible
%
9 He who walks blamelessly walks surely,
but he who perverts his ways will be found out.
  -- Proverbs 10:9 , World English Bible
%
10 One winking with the eye causes sorrow,
but a chattering fool will fall.
  -- Proverbs 10:10 , World English Bible
%
11 The mouth of the righteous is a spring of life,
but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
  -- Proverbs 10:11 , World English Bible
%
12 Hatred stirs up strife,
but love covers all wrongs.
  -- Proverbs 10:12 , World English Bible
%
13 Wisdom is found on the lips of him who has discernment,
but a rod is for the back of him who is void of understanding.
  -- Proverbs 10:13 , World English Bible
%
14 Wise men lay up knowledge,
but the mouth of the foolish is near ruin.
  -- Proverbs 10:14 , World English Bible
%
15 The rich man’s wealth is his strong city.
The destruction of the poor is their poverty.
  -- Proverbs 10:15 , World English Bible
%
16 The labor of the righteous leads to life.
The increase of the wicked leads to sin.
  -- Proverbs 10:16 , World English Bible
%
17 He is in the way of life who heeds correction,
but he who forsakes reproof leads others astray.
  -- Proverbs 10:17 , World English Bible
%
18 He who hides hatred has lying lips.
He who utters a slander is a fool.
  -- Proverbs 10:18 , World English Bible
%
19 In the multitude of words there is no lack of disobedience,
but he who restrains his lips does wisely.
  -- Proverbs 10:19 , World English Bible
%
20 The tongue of the righteous is like choice silver.
The heart of the wicked is of little worth.
  -- Proverbs 10:20 , World English Bible
%
21 The lips of the righteous feed many,
but the foolish die for lack of understanding.
  -- Proverbs 10:21 , World English Bible
%
22 Yahweh’s blessing brings wealth,
and he adds no trouble to it.
  -- Proverbs 10:22 , World English Bible
%
23 It is a fool’s pleasure to do wickedness,
but wisdom is a man of understanding’s pleasure.
  -- Proverbs 10:23 , World English Bible
%
24 What the wicked fear will overtake them,
but the desire of the righteous will be granted.
  -- Proverbs 10:24 , World English Bible
%
25 When the whirlwind passes, the wicked is no more;
but the righteous stand firm forever.
  -- Proverbs 10:25 , World English Bible
%
26 As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes,
so is the sluggard to those who send him.
  -- Proverbs 10:26 , World English Bible
%
27 The fear of Yahweh prolongs days,
but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.
  -- Proverbs 10:27 , World English Bible
%
28 The prospect of the righteous is joy,
but the hope of the wicked will perish.
  -- Proverbs 10:28 , World English Bible
%
29 The way of Yahweh is a stronghold to the upright,
but it is a destruction to the workers of iniquity.
  -- Proverbs 10:29 , World English Bible
%
30 The righteous will never be removed,
but the wicked will not dwell in the land.
  -- Proverbs 10:30 , World English Bible
%
31 The mouth of the righteous produces wisdom,
but the perverse tongue will be cut off.
  -- Proverbs 10:31 , World English Bible
%
32 The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,
but the mouth of the wicked is perverse.
  -- Proverbs 10:32 , World English Bible
%
